Privacy Policy for Smart Timeline

Last updated: 9/23/2024

Thank you for choosing Smart Timeline, developed by Evan's Oasis LLC ("we," "us," "our"). This Privacy Policy outlines our commitment to protect your privacy and explains our practices regarding the handling of information when you use our Smart Timeline app ("the app").

1. Information We Access

We do not store or share any of your personal data on our servers. The Smart Timeline app allows you to import your data directly from social media platforms such as Facebook to visualize your personal timeline. Although the app accesses your data online, no personal data is transmitted to our servers or third-party services, except as detailed below in section 4 regarding AI processing.

2. How the App Works

The app enables you to:

Import data from social media platforms to visualize and manage your personal timeline.
Process and categorize imported data, which remains locally on your device unless opted for AI analysis as specified.

3. AI Integration for Data Insights

Online AI Analysis: For users opting in, data may be processed by ChatGPT or a similar AI to generate insights. This process involves transmitting selected data securely to any of the well known online LLM creators such as Anthropic, Meta, OpenAI, and more..
Local AI Processing: In the future, we will provide an option to process data locally using AI, ensuring all data remains on your device.

4. Data Management and Security

Your data's security is crucial:

For online AI analysis, data is encrypted during transmission. We ensure our AI partners have robust privacy and security measures.
Locally processed data remains within your device, protected by your device’s security measures.

5. Your Rights and Choices

You have control over your data:

Data import: Choose which data to import from your social media platforms.
AI processing: Opt-in or opt-out of online AI analysis. Choose local processing once available.
Data deletion: Delete your data at any time from within the app.

6. Children’s Privacy

Smart Timeline does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. We will take steps to delete any such information inadvertently collected.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy periodically and will notify you of any significant changes. We encourage you to review this policy regularly.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: [Insert Contact Information].
